content: Repost from:@bryanongyyEver try authentic Lucknow cuisine? Around 550km southeast of New Delhi is a large city where the royal Nawabs (emperors) of Awadh Dynasty, best remembered for their refined and extravagant lifestyles, were well-known food connoisseurs that enjoyed many Lucknow delicacies that are gradually diluted today! Now you donâ€™t have to travel to India to taste the Lucknow cuisine, as just right in the heart of Orchard Road Singapore you can enjoy these delicacies that are very much fit for the Nawabs at @awadhdining!..AWADH Restaurant & Bar Singapore chefs belong to the famous Qureshi family of Master-chefs from Lucknow. Generations of this family have been trained to prepare exquisite cuisine using secret recipes that only the specially trained chefs have access to, hence it is impossible to replicate the taste. Famous cuisine like melt-in-the-mouth Galawat Kebabs (the King of Kebabs with over 25 spices), Murgh Pasanda, Seekh Niloferi, Sabz Shami and unique desserts like Shahi Tukda and Apple Jalebi, which are unique and never introduced in South East Asia before. author: omykampong
content: Saw a family of 3 discussing over the items at our Kek Ai Tiam aka provision shop at O'My Kampong Cafe. It's really heart warming to know that the uncle on the far right sharing with his children (we think) on why this is called Kek Ai Tiam in the olden days. "Kek Ai" is actually a Hokkien word used by the Chinese living in the Kampong Village, referring it as a provision shop. It is actually derived from the Malay word "Kedai" which means "shop". So when the Chinese heard from their Malay neighbours calling it Kedai, the Chinese community had come out with their own version of calling it "Kekai". Do you have any Kampong stories that you can share with us? Share with us on the comments section so the youngsters can also learn what is actually a Kampong Village in the olden days :). Have a Happy Friday Folks!#omykampong #omykampongcafe #cafebythepark #sengkangriversidepark #halalcafe #cafebyoldchangkee #makanbythepark #nofreecomedownnehmind #orderfromdelivery #grabfoodsg #deliveroosg #foodpandasg #kekaidiam #kedai #kekaitiam #kampongshop
